[2
Date: Wed, 18 Feb 1998 12:34:23 -0700
From: Hal Nash <HNASH@wwcc.cc.wy.us>

I think that the reporting of this is very appropriate. The key issue is
that mentioned in this post of people resorting to surface water more for
their source of water than groundwater. The arsenic poisoning of the
groundwater sets the stage for an outbreak of water-borne disease.
ProMED-mail reporting of this gives authorities at least a measure of
prediction of what might happen in the near future.
--
Hal B. Nash
Assistant Professor of Biology
